collect(bytes32).details: Collects the stability fee of the specified collateral pool. This function can be called by anyone. It updates the `debtAccumulatedRate` of the specified collateral pool based on the global and per-pool stability fee rates with respect to the last block that `collect` was called.

params._collateralPool: Collateral pool ID for which to collect the stability fee.

returns._debtAccumulatedRate: Updated debtAccumulatedRate for the specified collateral pool.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

userdoc.notice: A contract that acts as a collector for the stability fee. The stability fee is a fee that is collected from the minter of Fathom Stablecoin on a per-seconds basis. This fee is accumulated in the system as a surplus to settle any bad debt. The contract is Pausable, meaning it can be paused by the owner or governance to prevent fee collection temporarily. Stability fees are collected for each collateral pool separately.
